    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2019-05-07</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2019-05-30T15:45:38Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Medicare Enrollment Protection Act</strong></p> <p>This bill creates a special Medicare enrollment period for individuals enrolled in, or transitioning out of, continuation coverage under the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (COBRA)&#8212;a federal law that allows an individual to maintain health coverage following loss of coverage due to termination of employment or another qualifying event.</p> <p>The bill exempts such individuals from certain monthly premium increases associated with delaying Medicare coverage.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
